# Frontend environment. Copy to .env (or .env.local) and adjust.

# Base URL of the backend API.
# - Local dev: leave BLANK. The app uses same-origin "/api" and the Vite dev
#   server proxies it to the backend (see vite.config.ts → server.proxy).
#   Optionally set VITE_PROXY_TARGET if your backend isn't on http://localhost:5000.
# - Production (GitHub Pages): set VITE_API_URL to your hosted backend, e.g.
#   VITE_API_URL=https://mahabharat-api.onrender.com/api
# VITE_API_URL=
# VITE_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:5000
